<FIRST>r a PM-LesbianSlaying     11-07 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Lesbian Slaying,0198</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Who Killed Lesbian Lover Gets 12-year Prison Sentence</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge sentenced a woman who
fatally shot her lesbian lover to the minimum prison term, saying
he sympathized with her claim she acted in self-defense after years
of beatings.
   Annette Green _ whose defense centered on the unusual use of the
``battered wife'' syndrome in a relationship between two women _
was sentenced Monday to 12 years in prison for second-degree murder.
   ``Your background has been unusual,'' Circuit Judge Tom Waddell
said before imposing the minimum sentence allowed. ``I want you to
understand that I'm not angry with you.''
   The 30-year-old defendant and others at the trial testified she
suffered frequent severe beatings at the hands of Ivonne Julio, her
lover and roommate for 11 years. She shot Ms. Julio, 32, in the
face during an argument after a Halloween party in 1988.
   Assistant State Attorney Bob Johnson, who recommended a sentence
of 22 years, found the punishment inadequate, saying with parole
Ms. Green would ``probably get out in three'' years.
   ``I don't think that's appropriate for someone who killed
somebody,'' Johnson said.
