<HEAD>Cold Front in Pacific Northwest; Winds Howl in West's Mountains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front moving into the Pacific Northwest was expected to
bring another taste of winter to that region while winds howled
through the mountains of the West and parts of the Northwest.
   Advisories were posted for 3 to 6 additional inches of snow
Monday night for Idaho's northern mountains, and for for up to 4
more inches in Colorado's central mountains. Today, a wind advisory
was posted over the upper Snake River Plains of Idaho.
   High wind warnings were up today for the northwest mountains of
Wyoming, ande a high wind watch for the southeast mountains of
Idaho.
   Advisories for gale force winds Monday night were posted over
the coastal waters of Washington state. Snow advisories remained in
effect through Monday evening for Washington's Cascades and the
Oregon Cascades.
   Meanwhile, temperatures were unseasonably high in parts of
states along the Gulf of Mexico coast.
   Among the cities where record highs were set for the date:
Dallas-Fort Worth, 89 (87 in 1945); Fort Myers, Fla., 90 (89 in
1986); Pensacola, Fla., 82 (80 in 1909 and 1935); San Angelo,
Texas, 87 (86 in 1915); Shreveport, La., 86 (85 in 1980); and Waco,
Texas, 89 (87 in 1980).
   The nation's high Monday was 91 at Laredo, Texas.
   Showers and thunderstorms continued east of a cold front Monday,
extending from the western part of the Carolinas across northern
Georgia, Alabama, Mississippi, Louisiana and the upper Texas Gulf
Coast.
   Showers also reached from eastern Virginia across Delaware, as
well as northern and central New England, northern Iowa, southern
Minnesota and southern South Dakota.
   Rain extended along the Washington and Oregon coast, and from
the panhandle of Idaho into eastern Washington and western Montana.
   Other reports at 3 a.m. EST:
   _East: Albany, N.Y. fair; Atlanta 58 cloudy; Boston 49 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 66 foggy; Chattanooga 58 foggy; Cincinnati 46
partly cloudy; Cleveland 39 partly cloudy; Detroit 40 cloudy;
Hatteras 65 cloudy; Jacksonville 66 fair; Key West 76 fair;
Knoxville 49 foggy; Macon 62 partly cloudy; Miami 73 fair; New York
46 foggy; Philadelphia 46 foggy; Pittsburgh 36 fair; Portland, Me.,
47 partly cloudy; Richmond 56 foggy; Tampa 67 fair; Washington,
D.C. 53 foggy.
   _Central: Birmingham partly cloudy; Bismarck 30 fair; Chicago 42
rain; Denver 40 partly cloudy; Des Moines 37 fair; Indianapolis 45
showery; Kansas City 40 fair; Little Rock 69 foggy; Louisville 50
partly cloudy; Memphis 63 partly cloudy; Nashville 62 cloudy; New
Orleans 67 showery; North Platte 22 fair; Oklahoma City 54 fair;
Omaha 33 fair; Rapid City 34 cloudy; St. Louis 53 cloudy;
Minneapolis-St. Paul 42 partly cloudy; Sault Ste. Marie 33 cloudy;
San Antonio 73 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque fair; Anchorage 10 fair; Boise 40 partly
cloudy; Casper 38 cloudy; Fairbanks 7 fair; Great Falls 41 windy;
Honolulu 76 fair; Las Vegas 55 partly cloudy; Los Angeles 57 partly
cloudy; Medford 44 showery; Pendleton 53 partly cloudy; Phoenix 58
fair; Portland, Ore. 50 cloudy; Reno 35 fair; Salt Lake City 41
