said he would go to next month's meeting with Mikhail Gorbachev
with no initiatives to offer.
   ``I'd like to hear some specific suggestions,'' Bush said,
``besides triple the spending.'' He said he has no perception that
European allies are unhappy with the pace of his U.S.-Soviet
policies.
   
