<SECOND>PM-BRF--Yogurt Spill,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>It's Low-Fat, But It Slows You Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CROTON FALLS, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An interstate highway was slathered
with four flavors of yogurt early today after a delivery truck
slammed into a tractor-trailer in thick fog.
   Hundreds of cartons spilled onto Interstate 684 and broke,
closing the major commuting route in New York City's northern
suburbs for five hours. Firefighters washed the sticky substance
from the road just before rush hour.
   ``We were knee deep in yogurt,'' said Fire Chief Chris Ritchie.
   Police said traffic was slow afterward because of the
startlingly sweet smell of cherry, vanilla, peach and blueberry
yogurt.
   No serious injuries were reported in the collision.
