<TEXT>
   Stormie Jones, the 12-year-old Texas girl who
is the world's first and only surviving heart-liver transplant
recipient, is receiving a new drug to combat organ rejection.
   Stormie was admitted Friday to Children's Hospital of Pittsburgh
because she had become slightly jaundiced, said hospital
spokeswoman Lynn McMahon. She was listed in good condition Tuesday.
   Stormie, who received her transplant Feb. 14, 1984, is getting
FK 506, a new anti-rejection drug recently approved for testing by
the Federal Drug Administration.
