<FIRST>u a PM-NightStalker     11-07 0205</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Night Stalker,0210</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Night Stalker' Sentenced to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard Ramirez, the ``Night Stalker'' who
butchered or raped more than a dozen people in an orgy of violence
that terrorized Southern California in 1985, was sentenced to death
in the gas chamber today.
   Superior Court Judge Michael Michael A. Tynan followed the
recommendation of the jury that convicted the devil-worshiping
29-year-old on Sept. 20.
   In the courtroom before his sentencing, Ramirez, wearing dark
glases, uttered a rambling, nearly inaudible statement that ended
with the words: ``Lucifer dwells within us all.''
   The killer, who entered unlocked houses late at night to attack
people in their beds, was convicted of 13 murders and 30 other
felonies, including rape, burglary and sodomy.
   The jurors, some of whom said the defendant had tried to
intimidate them during the trial by sneering and glaring at them,
recommended Oct. 4 that he be sentenced to death rather than life
in prison.
   A snarling, gravelly-voiced Ramirez had sneered at the
possibility of being sentenced to death. ``Big deal. Death comes
with the territory,'' he told reporters after the jury's
recommendation. ``See you in Disneyland.''
   After his conviction, Ramirez flashed a two-fingered ``devil
sign'' at photographers and muttered, ``Evil.''
</TEXT>
