<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--MissileLaunch     11-07 0153</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Missile Launch,0157</SECOND>
<HEAD>Unarmed Minuteman 3 Missile Successfully Launched to Pacific Test
Range</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 16-year-old Minuteman
3 missile on Tuesday delivered dummy warheads to Pacific Ocean
targets 4,200 miles from its California launch site, the Air Force
said.
   Thirty minutes after the 8:17 a.m. liftoff, the missile's
unarmed re-entry vehicles were tracked to targets in the Kwajalein
Missile Range.
   It was the 141st in a series of operational test launches of the
Minuteman 3 weapon system, an Air Force statement said.
   The missile had been in the Air Force inventory since Nov. 15,
1973.
   The launch was conducted by an airborne missile launch crew from
the 2nd Airborne Command Control Squadron at Offutt Air Force Base,
Neb.
   Airborne launch crews, flying aboard specially modified Boeing
EC-135 jets, are maintained as a backup in case ground crews are
unable to send launch commands to Minuteman missiles.
