<FILEID>AP-NR-11-07-89 1852EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w AM-AirlineReport     11-07 0139</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Airline Report,140</SECOND>
<HEAD>Airlines Log Best On-Time Performance Since April</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Major U.S. airlines in September logged their
best on-time performance since April, the Transportation Department
said Tuesday.
   The department's monthly consumer report also showed a decrease
in the number of mishandled baggage complaints against airlines, but
a slight increase in other complaints.
   The data for September showed that the 12 largest carriers
reported 79.6 percent of their flights operating on time, an
improvement over the 74.6 percent that operated on time in August.
   It was the best record since April's 83.4 percent.
   Mishandled baggage complaints filed against carriers averaged
7.25 reports per 1,000 passengers in September, compared with 8.19
in August, the report said.
   Consumer complaints against all airlines increased from 1,104 in
September to 1,143 in October, the only figures available for last
month.
</TEXT>
