<HEAD>Panel Recommends Full Senate Confirm Two to NRC Posts</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Senate Environment and Public Works
Committee on Tuesday unanimously recommended confirmation of Forrest
J. Remick as a member of the Nuclear Regulatory Commission and David
C. Williams as the commission's inspector general.
   Remick, most recently chairman of the NRC's Advisory Committee on
Reactor Safeguards, would fill a vacancy created by the retirement
last June of Lando W. Zech Jr. as chairman.
   Commissioner Kenneth Carr replaced Zech as chairman July 1.
   Remick was an administrative judge on the Atomic Safety and
Licensing Board for 10 years, director of the commission's Office of
Policy Evaluation for a year and spent seven years on the
commission's safeguards advisory committee.
   Williams has no experience in nuclear regulation but served in
military intelligency agencies, the Secret Service, the Labor
Department's office of labor racketeering, and, most recently, the
General Accounting Office's special investigations unit.
