<HEAD>Explosion at Recreation Center Injures 27</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosion and fire ripped through a recreation
center in the resort town of Margate Tuesday, injuring 25 children
and two firemen.
   Divisional fire officer Kevin Simmonds said firemen were summoned
when a small blaze was discovered in a sauna-bath unit and there was
a blast as firefighters arrived.
   Traffic officer Peter Hall was credited with saving many lives.
   Police said he shepherded the children, aged 11-16, away from the
smoking sauna unit just before the explosion that sent a wall of
fire through the building.
   ``If he had not moved the children away there would almost
certainly have been fatalities,'' a police spokesman said.
   Most of the victims were treated at a hospital for minor burns
and injuries but one boy and a fireman were in serious condition and
were transferred to a burn unit, official said.
   A spokesman for the Thanet District Council in Margate, 70 miles
east of London, said an investigation was under way to determine the
cause of the explosion.
