<SECOND>AM-China-Tainted Drink,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Death Toll from Tainted Drink Reaches 34</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rice wine heavily tainted with methyl alcohol has
killed 34 people in the southern China province of Guangdong, an
official daily said Wednesday.
   The China Daily said 130 others have been hospitalized after
consuming the drink, which contained 350 times the state safety
standards for methyl alcohol.
   Seventeen people have been arrested for making and selling the
contaminated wine, the report said.
   The deaths occurred in Zhaoqing, a city about 45 miles west of
the provincial capital of Canton.
   The official China News Service said earlier that Zhaoqing
officials from one city district searched more than 60 businesses
Saturday and confiscated 900 pounds of the poison alcohol.
