<HEAD>Texas Instruments Signs Investment Agreement With Italy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Texas Instruments Inc. signed an agreement with the
Italian government Tuesday for $1.2 billion of investments in
southern Italy over a period of four years.
   The U.S. electronics manufacturer said that $715 million will be
paid for by Italy's Ministry for Development of the South.
   Officials said the investments will be used for the construction
of a semi-conductor plant at Avezzano, in the Abruzzi region, about
