   ``The expansion of operations in Italy will add approximately
1,000 new jobs to the already 2,000 existing in our country,'' said
Roberto Schisano, managing director of Texas Instruments Italy.
   He signed the agreement with Riccardo Misasi, Italian Minister
for Development of the South.
   Texas Instruments will own all facilities.
