<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Updates throughout with closing prices.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stocks in London rose Tuesday in slow trading.
Technical factors and less fear of an imminent hike in British
interest rates helped prices.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index finished up
8.6 points, or 0.4 percent, at 2,178.2, its session high.
   The key index advanced throughout the session after posting its
low in early trading. Dealers linked the rise to the lack of
follow-through selling after Wall Street's sharp losses on Monday
and New York's modest rebound before London's close.
   The Financial Times 30-share index finished 6.8 points higher at
1,753.8. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 2.35 points to
close at 1,204.38.
   Volume was still light at 416.9 million shares traded, although
better than Monday's volume of 323.4 million shares.
